                        Stuart
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1948v07</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d595</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">595</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1948-12-31T01:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1948-12-31T01:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-12-31T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-12-31T01:00:00-05:00" n="595" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d595">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12–3148: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-12-31T14:00:00+08:00">December 31, 1948—2 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 3:31 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2678. Conference of military leaders which has been taking place Nanking was
                    called by Generalissimo we believe with view strengthening his determination
                    continue resistance. Fu Tso-yi did not attend and Pai Chung-hsi who had
                    telegraphed Generalissimo advice to retire could not of course attend. Those
                    attending seemed to have strengthened his determination to carry on
                    [approximately 13 letters garbled] we know of Chang Chi-chung’s desire for
                    cessation hostilities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
